<inglise> Guidelines for the certification audit of the EAGGF accounts </inglise>
<eesti> SUUNISED EAGGFi RAAMATUPIDAMISARVESTUST ATESTEERIVA AUDITI TEGEMISEKS </eesti>
<inglise> Subject: Guideline N&deg;4 - Intervention operations and stocks </inglise>
<eesti> Teema: Suunis nr 4 - sekkumistegevus ja -varud </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Background </inglise>
<eesti> Taust </eesti>
<inglise> This guideline N&deg; 4 emphasises the audit assurance, which must be obtained by the certifying body from the systems and procedures in place in the paying agency. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev suunis nr 4 keskendub auditeerimiskindlusele, mille atesteeriv asutus auditeerimisel saab makseasutuses kehtivast s&uuml;steemist ja korrast. </eesti>
<inglise> In particular these procedures and systems must comply with Regulation 2148/96 (evaluating and monitoring public intervention stocks). </inglise>
<eesti> Need s&uuml;steemid ja kord peavad vastama m&auml;&auml;rusele 2148/96 (riiklike sekkumisvarude hindamine ja kontroll). </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Regulatory requirements </inglise>
<eesti> Reguleerivad n&otilde;uded (1) </eesti>
<inglise> According to art.3(3) of R.1663/95 the Certifying Body is required to report on: </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse 1663/95 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele 3 on atesteeriv asutus kohustatud esitama aruande selle kohta: </eesti>
<inglise> "whether the statements of... intervention operations... are a materially true, complete and accurate record of the operations charged to the Fund"; and </inglise>
<eesti> "kas... sekkumistegevuse aruannetes on fondi poolt rahastatavaid meetmeid kajastatud terviklikult, t&auml;pselt ja t&otilde;ep&auml;raselt"; ja </eesti>
<inglise> "whether the financial interests of the Community are properly protected as regards... intervention stocks...". </inglise>
<eesti> "kas &uuml;henduse finantshuvid seoses... sekkumisvarudega... on korralikult kaitstud". </eesti>
<inglise> These requirements mean that (i) the Certifying Body must not only obtain assurance that the paying agency has established appropriate procedures for ensuring compliance with community rules (including the accreditation requirements of point 8 of the annex to R.1663/95), but that (ii) it must also audit the statements of intervention operations to the extent necessary to enable a clear expression of opinion on them, and that (iii) it must obtain direct audit evidence of the existence of stocks. </inglise>
<eesti> Need n&otilde;uded t&auml;hendavad, et i) atesteeriv asutus peab mitte ainult saama kindluse, et makseasutus on kehtestanud &uuml;henduse eeskirjade (kaasa arvatud m&auml;&auml;ruse 1663/95 lisa punkti 8 akrediteerimiskriteeriumid) j&auml;rgimise tagamiseks sobiva korra, vaid ii) samuti auditeerima sekkumistegevuse aruandeid m&auml;&auml;ral, mis on vajalik nende kohta selge arvamuse v&auml;ljendamiseks, ja et iii) ta peab saama auditi otsese t&otilde;endusmaterjali auditeerimist&otilde;endid varude olemasolu kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Scope of the audit work </inglise>
<eesti> Auditeerimistegevuse ulatus </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Assurance that the paying agency has established appropriate procedures for ensuring compliance with community rules </inglise>
<eesti> Kindlus selles, et makseasutus on kehtestanud sobiva korra &uuml;henduse eeskirjade j&auml;rgimise tagamiseks </eesti>
<inglise> For all intervention commodities the Certifying Body will determine whether the paying agency has established adequate procedures and practises to ensure that the following key control objectives are met to ensure that: </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;igi sekkumiskaupade puhul teeb atesteeriv asutus kindlaks, kas makseasutuses on kehtestatud asjakohane kord j&auml;rgmiste p&otilde;hiliste kontrollieesm&auml;rkide t&auml;itmiseks, millega tagada, et: </eesti>
<inglise> - the product accepted by the relevant Management Committee is accepted into intervention and supplied by the authorized tenderer at the tendered price; </inglise>
<eesti> - vastava korralduskomitee heakskiidetud toode v&otilde;etakse sekkumisvarudesse vastu ja volitatud pakkuja tarnib need pakutud hinnaga; </eesti>
<inglise> - the product taken into intervention complies with the classification and quality set out in the tender; </inglise>
<eesti> - sekkumisvarudesse v&otilde;etud toode vastab pakkumises t&auml;psustatud liigitusele ja kvaliteedile; </eesti>
<inglise> - the total weight of product taken into intervention complies with the tender; </inglise>
<eesti> - sekkumisvarudesse v&otilde;etud toote kogukaal vastab pakkumisele; </eesti>
<inglise> - all stocks are physically secure, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;ik varud on f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt kaitstud, </eesti>
<inglise> - storekeepers keep computerized records of intervention stocks, </inglise>
<eesti> - laopidajad peavad sekkumisvarude kohta arvutip&otilde;hist raamatupidamist, </eesti>
<inglise> - stock movement figures are accurately and completely recorded by the paying agency and by the store and technical costs are properly charged; </inglise>
<eesti> - makseasutus ja ladu dokumenteerivad t&auml;pselt ning t&auml;ielikult andmed varude liikumise kohta ja n&auml;itavad tehnilised kulud n&otilde;uetekohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise> - sales and the corresponding amount received are conform with Community regulations; </inglise>
<eesti> - m&uuml;&uuml;k ja vastav laekumine vastavad &uuml;henduse m&auml;&auml;rustele; </eesti>
<inglise> - all transactions are correctly calculated, authorized in advance, paid/received within the required time limits, correctly recorded in the monthly declarations and reconciliations between the various books are evidenced and supported by working papers. </inglise>
<eesti> - k&otilde;ik tehingud on &otilde;igesti arvutatud, eelnevalt kinnitatud, makstud/laekunud m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul, igakuistes aruannetes n&otilde;uetekohaselt dokumenteeritud ning vastavuse kontrollimine mitmesuguste arvestusraamatute vahel on kinnitatud ja t&otilde;endatud t&ouml;&ouml;dokumentidega. </eesti>
<inglise> Particular attention should be given to the controls and procedures in place to ensure the completeness and accuracy of input to the F-audit and the statements of intervention operations. </inglise>
<eesti> Erilist t&auml;helepanu tuleks p&ouml;&ouml;rata olemasolevatele kontrollieeskirjadele, et tagada finantsauditi sisendmaterjalide ning sekkumistegevuse aruande t&auml;ielikkus ja t&auml;psus. </eesti>
<inglise> Annex I presents some examples of the points to be verified by the Certifying Body. </inglise>
<eesti> I lisa esitab m&otilde;ned n&auml;ited punktidest, mida atesteeriv asutus peab kontrollima. </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Audit evidence of the existence of stocks </inglise>
<eesti> Auditi t&otilde;endusmaterjal varude olemasolu kohta </eesti>
<inglise> The key issue for the certifying body for obtaining direct audit evidence of the existence of stocks is: </inglise>
<eesti> Atesteeriva asutuse p&otilde;hi&uuml;lesandeks varude olemasolu kohta auditi otsese t&otilde;endusmaterjali saamisel on: </eesti>
<inglise> - to ensure the correct implementation of Regulation 2148/96 by reviewing the paying agency's procedures in respect of intervention stocks; </inglise>
<eesti> - tagada m&auml;&auml;ruse 2148/96 n&otilde;uetekohane rakendamine kontrollides makseasutuse korda seoses sekkumisvarudega; </eesti>
<inglise> - to review the current year's reports on stocktaking as carried out by the paying agency's technical and internal audit services; </inglise>
<eesti> - vaadata &uuml;le jooksva aasta inventuuriaruanded, mille on teinud makseasutuse tehnilised ja siseauditi talitused; </eesti>
<inglise> - to participate in some selected stocktakings. </inglise>
<eesti> - osaleda teatavates valitud inventuurides. </eesti>
<inglise> With regard to physical inspections, the following key points need to be stressed: </inglise>
<eesti> Pidades silmas f&uuml;&uuml;silist kontrolli, tuleb r&otilde;hutada j&auml;rgmisi punkte: </eesti>
<inglise> - the physical examination must cover the quantity of the goods selected, and the general storage conditions at the store, </inglise>
<eesti> - f&uuml;&uuml;siline kontroll peab h&otilde;lmama valitud kauba koguse ja &uuml;ldised ladustamistingimused, </eesti>
<inglise> - the starting point of the inventory is the performance of a reconciliation between the paying agency's stock records and the statements received from the stores, </inglise>
<eesti> - inventuur algab makseasutuse laoarvestuse ja ladudest saadud aruannete v&otilde;rdlemisest, </eesti>
<inglise> - the lots or other identifiable units to be inspected must be selected from the paying agency's stock records before visiting the store, </inglise>
<eesti> - kontrollitavad partiid v&otilde;i muud eristatavad &uuml;hikud tuleb valida makseasutuse laoarvestusest enne lao k&uuml;lastamist, </eesti>
<inglise> - the storekeeper should not be informed in advance about the sample selected for inspection, </inglise>
<eesti> - laopidajale ei tohi kontrollimiseks valitud valimist ette teatada, </eesti>
<inglise> - on arrival at the store, a reconciliation should be made between the information already available at the paying agency and the store records and the location of stock, </inglise>
<eesti> - lattu j&otilde;udes tuleks juba makseasutuses saadud teavet v&otilde;rrelda laodokumentidega ja varude asukohaga, </eesti>
<inglise> - the lots or other identifiable units selected from the paying agency's records must be counted completely. </inglise>
<eesti> - makseasutuse dokumentidest valitud partiid v&otilde;i muud eristatavad &uuml;hikud tuleb t&auml;ielikult loendada. </eesti>
<inglise> Counting only 5 % of the quantity of each selected unit does not provide any assurance on the complete presence of the selected stocks, </inglise>
<eesti> Iga valitud &uuml;hiku kogusest ainult 5% loendamine ei anna kindlust valitud varude t&auml;ielikus olemasolus, </eesti>
<inglise> - each store must be inspected at least once every year (article 4 in R. 2148/96), </inglise>
<eesti> - iga ladu tuleb kontrollida v&auml;hemalt kord aastas (m&auml;&auml;ruse 2148/96 artikkel 4), </eesti>
<inglise> - the sample of 5 percent (annex III to R. 2148/96) to be checked is per store e.g. in each store 5 % needs to be checked, </inglise>
<eesti> - kontrollitav 5-protsendine valim lao kohta (m&auml;&auml;ruse 2148/96 III lisa) t&auml;hendab, et igas laos tuleb kontrollida 5% varudest, </eesti>
<inglise> - the inspection body or its representative must issue a report on each inspection they have carried out at least once a year and a summary report (article 5 in R. 2148/96), </inglise>
<eesti> - kontrolliasutus v&otilde;i selle esindaja koostab akti iga kontrolli kohta, mida tehakse v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kord aastas, ja koondaruande (m&auml;&auml;ruse 2148/96 artikkel 5), </eesti>
<inglise> The results of the inspections must be taken into account and corrections must be made where necessary. </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrolli tulemusi tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta ja teha vajaduse korral parandused. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 of R. 2148/96 clearly states that the storekeeper shall be responsible for any differences established between the quantities in store and the details given in the stock statements sent to the intervention agency (point 1 of art. 6). </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse 2148/96 artikkel 6 s&auml;testab selgelt, et laopidaja vastutab k&otilde;ikide erinevuste eest, mis on avastatud ladustatud koguste ja sekkumisametile saadetud aruannete vahel. </eesti>
<inglise> Where the quantities missing exceed those permitted by the tolerance(s) applicable, the total shall normally be charged to the storekeeper (see point 2 in art. 6). </inglise>
<eesti> Kui puuduvad kogused &uuml;letavad kohaldatava lubatud h&auml;lbe, arvestatakse seda kui laopidajale tekkinud selgitamata p&otilde;hjustega kadu (vt artikli 6 punkti 2). </eesti>
<inglise> Before the end of the EAGGF year the following points need to be examined: </inglise>
<eesti> Enne EAGGFi aasta l&otilde;ppu tuleb uurida j&auml;rgmisi punkte: </eesti>
<inglise> - to extent to which inventory controls need to be performed by the certifying body at the end of the EAGGF year should be based on the reliability of the control system at the paying agency. </inglise>
<eesti> - m&auml;&auml;r, mille ulatuses atesteeriv asutus peab tegema kaubavarude kontrolli EAGFFi aasta l&otilde;pul, peaks p&otilde;hinema makseasutuse kontrollis&uuml;steemi usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsusel. </eesti>
<inglise> A large scale examination is needed in case of serious doubts about the reliability of the system or where there is no cyclical examination. </inglise>
<eesti> Ulatuslikku kontrolli on vaja t&otilde;siste kahtluste korral s&uuml;steemi usaldatavuse osas v&otilde;i juhul, kui puudub perioodiline kontroll. </eesti>
<inglise> However, the certifying body should consider what actions they need to undertake in order to receive direct audit evidence of the existence of stocks (i.e. to what extent they should participate in the inventory control checks during the EAGGF year and at the end of the EAGGF year), </inglise>
<eesti> Atesteeriv asutus peaks kaaluma, milliseid meetmeid on vaja v&otilde;tta, et saada auditi otsene t&otilde;endusmaterjal varude olemasolu kohta (st millisel m&auml;&auml;ral nad peaksid osalema inventuuri kontrollis EAGGFi aasta jooksul ja EAGGFi aasta l&otilde;pul), </eesti>
<inglise> - particular attention should be paid to the controls and procedures in place to ensure the completeness and accuracy of input to the F-audit system (the system provided by the commission to run intervention storage expenditure) and the statements of intervention operations. </inglise>
<eesti> - erilist t&auml;helepanu tuleks p&ouml;&ouml;rata olemasolevatele kontrollieeskirjadele, et tagada finantsauditi s&uuml;steemi (komisjoni etten&auml;htud s&uuml;steem sekkumisvarude ladustamiskulude kontrollimiseks) sisendmaterjalide ning sekkumistegevuse aruannete t&auml;ielikkus ja t&auml;psus. </eesti>
<inglise> - the certifying body should ensure a proper continuity of the stock records i.e. previous year's closing position and current year's starting position per product should be correct. </inglise>
<eesti> - atesteeriv asutus peaks tagama laoarvestuse n&otilde;uetekohase j&auml;tkuvuse, st eelmise aasta l&otilde;ppseis ja jooksva aasta algusseis toote kohta peaksid olema &otilde;iged. </eesti>
<inglise> In case of differences, the explanations need to be sought and, in case of difficulties in verifying the position, the situation should be fully noted in the audit report. </inglise>
<eesti> Erinevuste puhul tuleb leida nende p&otilde;hjused ja kui seisu t&otilde;endada on keeruline, tuleb auditeerimisaruandesse teha olukorrast t&auml;ielik &uuml;levaade. </eesti>
<inglise> The audit report should present a clear expression of opinion on each of the F-audit tables and on each of the statements of intervention operations. </inglise>
<eesti> Auditeerimisaruandes peaks iga finantsauditi tabeli ja iga sekkumistegevuse aruande kohta olema esitatud selge arvamus. </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Accreditation review </inglise>
<eesti> Akrediteerimine </eesti>
<inglise> Annex II indicates the audit criteria and matters of potential significance relevant to intervention operations which are to be addressed by the Certifying Body in the context of accreditation review. </inglise>
<eesti> II lisas on esitatud auditi kriteeriumid ja sekkumistegevusega seotud olulised k&uuml;simused, mida atesteeriv asutus v&otilde;ib k&auml;sitleda seoses akrediteerimisega. </eesti>
<inglise> The chosen example is beef intervention. </inglise>
<eesti> Valitud n&auml;ide on veiseliha sekkumisvaru. </eesti>
<inglise> ANNEX I </inglise>
<eesti> I LISA </eesti>
<inglise> Examples of certain points to be verified by the Certifying Body with regard to the substantive testing of a sample of items from statements of intervention operations (tables 1 to 10). </inglise>
<eesti> N&auml;ited teatavatest punktidest, mida atesteeriv asutus peab kontrollima, pidades silmas sekkumistegevuse aruannetest v&otilde;etud &uuml;hikute valimi sisulist kontrollimist (tabelid 1 - 10) </eesti>
<inglise> Purchases: reconciliation for the month concerned between the Paying Agency purchase records for quantity and quality to the relevant tender and to store invoices for quantities claimed to be in store and with store records. </inglise>
<eesti> Ostud: k&otilde;nealuse kuu makseasutuse ostudokumentide v&otilde;rdlemine asjakohase pakkumise koguse ja kvaliteediga ning v&auml;idetavalt ladustatud koguste v&otilde;rdlemine laoarvete ja laodokumentidega. </eesti>
<inglise> Sales/transfers: reconciliation for the month concerned between the Paying Agency sales/transfers records for quantity and quality to store invoices for quantities claimed to be in store and with store records. </inglise>
<eesti> M&uuml;&uuml;k/&uuml;leandmine: k&otilde;nealuse kuu makseasutuse m&uuml;&uuml;gi/&uuml;leandmisdokumentide v&otilde;rdlemine koguse ja kvaliteediga ning v&auml;idetavalt ladustatud koguste v&otilde;rdlemine laoarvete ja laodokumentidega. </eesti>
<inglise> Transport costs: reconciliation for the month concerned between the Paying Agency records for transport costs to transport invoices and to the Paying Agency records for purchases and sales/transfers (verifying that the transport costs are calculated on the basis of actual costs and by reference to an agreed tariff). </inglise>
<eesti> Veokulud: k&otilde;nealuse kuu makseasutuse veokulude dokumentide v&otilde;rdlemine veoarvetega ning makseasutuse ostu- ja m&uuml;&uuml;gi/&uuml;leandmisdokumentidega (kontrollides, et veokulud on arvutatud tegelike kulude alusel ja viidates kokkulepitud tariifile). </eesti>
<inglise> Losses/gains: reconciliation between the weight of a given lot established upon intake at an intervention store and the total weight of the same lot established upon outtake. </inglise>
<eesti> Kaod/kasum: konkreetse partii sekkumislattu v&otilde;tmise ajal kindlaks tehtud kaalu v&otilde;rdlemine sama partii v&auml;ljav&otilde;tmise ajal kindlaks tehtud kogukaaluga. </eesti>
<inglise> Evaluation of the reasons for any difference and confirmation that the losses are recorded on the correct date and in the correct column (removals without physical movement) in table 8. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga erinevuse p&otilde;hjuse hindamine ja kinnitamine, et kadu on dokumenteeritud &otilde;igel kuup&auml;eval ning tabeli 8 &otilde;iges veerus (eemaldamine ilma f&uuml;&uuml;silise liikumiseta). </eesti>
<inglise> Determine that the correct accounting rules were followed when establishing the value of the loss credited to the EAGGF accounts (R 3597/90). </inglise>
<eesti> Kindlaks tegemine, et EAGGFi raamatupidamisarvestusse kantud kao v&auml;&auml;rtuse m&auml;&auml;ramisel j&auml;rgiti n&otilde;uetekohaseid raamatupidamiseeskirju (m&auml;&auml;rus 3597/90). </eesti>
<inglise> Verify that losses have been correctly allocated in tables 2 and 7 between the categories for identifiable and unidentifiable loss. </inglise>
<eesti> Kontroll, et kaod on tabelites 2 ja 7 &otilde;igesti jaotatud tuvastatud p&otilde;hjustega kadude ja tuvastamata p&otilde;hjustega kadude vahel. </eesti>
<inglise> Technical costs: reconciliation between the monthly reports forwarded by the storekeeper according to R. 2148/96 and the records held by the Paying Agency. </inglise>
<eesti> Tehnilised kulud: vastavalt m&auml;&auml;rusele 2148/96 laopidaja saadetud kuuaruannete v&otilde;rdlemine makseasutuses peetava dokumentatsiooniga. </eesti>
<inglise> Verify that products taken over by the purchaser and removed from store have been correctly allocated in table 8 between the categories for products taken over or removed with physical movement and without physical movement (tables 3, 8 and 9). </inglise>
<eesti> Kontroll, et ostja poolt &uuml;le v&otilde;etud ja laost v&auml;lja viidud tooted on tabelis 8 &otilde;igesti jaotatud f&uuml;&uuml;silise liikumisega ning ilma f&uuml;&uuml;silise liikumiseta &uuml;le v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i v&auml;lja viidud toodeteks (tabelid 3, 8 ja 9). </eesti>
<inglise> Financing costs: verify that the financing costs charged to the EAGGF (table 4) are based upon the figures presented in a correct table 8, and verify the correct average value and the correct rate of interest. </inglise>
<eesti> Rahastamiskulud: kontroll, et EAGGFi kantavad rahastamiskulud (tabel 4) p&otilde;hinevad tabelis 8 n&otilde;uetekohaselt esitatud arvudel, ja &otilde;ige keskmise v&auml;&auml;rtuse ning &otilde;ige intressim&auml;&auml;ra kinnitamine. (2) </eesti>
